## Error Handling

Swift provides a powerful way to handle errors using the `throw`, `try`, and `catch` keywords.

### Defining Error Types

```swift
enum ValidationError: Error {
    case emptyField(String)
    case invalidEmail
    case passwordTooShort(minLength: Int)
}
```

### Throwing Functions

```swift
func validateEmail(_ email: String) throws {
    guard !email.isEmpty else {
        throw ValidationError.emptyField("email")
    }
    guard email.contains("@") else {
        throw ValidationError.invalidEmail
    }
}
```

### Handling Errors

```swift
do {
    try validateEmail("user@example.com")
    print("Valid email!")
} catch ValidationError.emptyField(let field) {
    print("\(field) cannot be empty")
} catch ValidationError.invalidEmail {
    print("Invalid email format")
} catch {
    print("Unknown error: \(error)")
}
```

### Optional Try

```swift
let result = try? validateEmail("test") // Returns nil on error
```

